A couple stories to add...<br>
<br>
My girlfriend (cleric) got pummeled by a frenzied griffon in eastern wastes.  I had a CH'ing missionary on my hands along with a dire wolf.<br>
<br>
She fell to the ground just as I killed the griffon with Dimentia.  She had cast Superior heal on herself, got interrupted, fell to the ground and was bleading to death.  She was at 2 purple bubbles when she regained concentration and healed herself while laying on the ground!  I've never seen this happen in 2 years of play.  This happened 2 months ago or so.<br>
<br>
A second time a level 2 enchantress was fighting outside Felwithe.  I had an eye on her as I have a soft spot for newbie enchanters (until I find them wearing a siren scale anyways).<br>
<br>
She, of course, met an angry Orc Pawn that was quickly slain by the guards as she trained them.  The Orc though did get his wacks in and dropped her unconscious to the ground.  Playing an enchanter at the time, I could only try to save her life by using bandaids.  I applied one bandage to her as she lay on the ground and next thing, POP!  She stands up and is completly healed =)<br>
<br>
My eyes watered I was laughing so hard...<br>
