<br>
The first time I was level 56, pulling in the crypt area in sebilis.  Well, the cleric's aegolism wore off just as I ate two tasty harm touches from a couple krup ghoul knights.  Needless to say, I arrived at the party's feet at well under a bubble of health, and the cleric had the audacity to begin casting 'complete heal.'<br>
<br>
Thinking quickly, i hit /disc nimble, but I'd spent that discipline in an encounter involving a few skeletal guards in front of the emperor, so I knew I was dead.  My pull comes to the party, and the enchanter gets a good ae stun off, buying the CH another second or three; but one krup woke up while she was busy mezzing the other one, and he promptly knocked me unconscious with one hit.<br>
<br>
Four hits later, as the frog swings, I had managed to riposte, dodge, and get missed twice, and the cleric's CH went off.<br>
<br>
The second time was in an AE group.  There is one thing about AE groups that you must know if you've never been in one.  The puller must have a deathwish; I have found no upper limit on the number of targets that can be AE stun/PBae'd to death at once, excepting the usual resists.  And I really did try.  On one pull, I managed to get absolutely every frog in a straight line path between the disco room and the bar room, with one quick detour into the exit to collect some golems, simultaneously. <br>
<br>
Naturally, when I get back to the group with half of sebilis on my heels, the Cleric (the SAME cleric as the previous crypt group) decides now's a good time to Make the Rogue Sweat (tm).  You guessed it; twenty or so frogs, four golems, and a pox scarab having me for lunch simultaneously, and I get the complete heal.  I did go unconscious first.  Amazingly, I survived, and so did the enchanter 11 seconds later when it was his turn for the HP bar to go purple.<br>
